CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 7, 1959, pg. 2, reads: "'Nothing to Worry About' - That's what Fifth Ward Democratic Chairman Robert E. (Pappy) Williams told City Councilman Paul F. Jones at a midday meeting in 10th District polling place Tuesday. 'Pappy' was right, as Councilman Jones was next to the highest vote-getter in his own ward, and third in the city-wide voting, and won his second tern in City Council. - Harris Photo."Cutline for image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 11, 1964, pg. 3, reads: "KEY POLITICIANS - In years past, election day in the Fifth Ward found scenes like the above, as Ward Chairman Williams and City Councilman Paul F. Jones, now also deceased, visited Hill polling places.  - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Paul Jones and Robert E. "Pappy" Williams wearing Democratic campaign card with button reading "Barr for mayor" standing in front of voting booth
